msgid "Gateway marked offline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/gateways.rst:125
msgid ""
"When a gateway is marked offline, always check if the monitor address is "
"reachable via the correct interface first. You can use "
":menuselection:`Interfaces->Diagnostics->Ping` to test connectivity. In "
"case the monitor address is not in the same subnet as the interface, also"
" check if there's a static route "
"(:menuselection:`System->Routes->Status`) available which sends the "
"requested traffic to the correct upstream gateway."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/gateways.rst:130
msgid ""
"There should always be a :code:`dpinger` process active, which you can "
"check on the services page "
"(:menuselection:`System->Diagnostics->Services`), finally if all seems to"
" be running you can deep dive into the packets leaving the interface, if "
"dpinger is active, there should be ICMP packets heading to your monitor "
"address, which you can inspect using "
":menuselection:`Interfaces->Diagnostics->Packet Capture`."
msgstr ""

